Package gui.panels.subcontrolpanels

Class Summary
BreakPanel The BreakPanel is responsible for initiating and managing non-normative situations.
GlassInfoPanel The GlassInfoPanel class displays information on glass in production
GlassMakePanel The GlassMakePanel class contains buttons allowing the user to select what type of glass to produce.
GlassSelectPanel The GlassSelectPanel class contains buttons allowing the user to select what type of glass to produce.
LogoPanel The logo panel is a place holder
NonNormPanel The NonNormPanel is responsible for initiating and managing non-normative situations.
StatePanel The StatePanel controls the factory's run state and the speed of the factory.
TitlePanel The TitlePanel holds a title "Factory Control"
TracePanel TracePanel class represents a JPanel that is used for displaying the messaging between backend agents.
TracePanelMessage TracePanelMessage represents a message and contains the agent that sent the message.
